A blanket
factory was on fire on Wednesday afternoon at Bunsen Street and Albertina
Sisulu Street in Joburg Industria. JMPD
spokesman, superintendent, Wayne Minnaar said fortunately, everyone evacuated
before they could be injured.  "Kelvin
Street was blocked off by JMPD between Bunsen Street and Albertina Sisulu
Street for emergency personal and for the firetrucks," said Minnaar. "The
fire started after 2pm today and the cause of the fire will be
investigated," he added.  